The article discusses various international agreements and initiatives aimed at countering nuclear terrorism and improving nuclear security. These include the International Convention for the Suppression of Acts of Nuclear Terrorism, the Convention on the Physical Protection of Nuclear Material, United Nations Security Council Resolution 1540, the IAEA Nuclear Security Plan, and the Global Initiative to Combat Nuclear Terrorism. The article also mentions the role of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) in providing guidance and assistance to member states in implementing these measures. Additionally, it highlights the importance of developing a Design Basis Threat (DBT) and conducting peer reviews through the International Physical Protection Advisory Service (IPPAS). The article concludes by mentioning the G-8 Global Partnership Against the Spread of Weapons and Materials of Mass Destruction, which focuses on nonproliferation, disarmament, counterterrorism, and nuclear safety issues through cooperative projects.